				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">funny how a class cries when a bug they come to rely on gets nerfed..
<br />

<br />
as one of the magi's pointed out, he never goes OOM because he doesnt chain cast.. if you are chain casting, your mana should go -down- not up, unless it's the real cannibalize spell.. but shamen pay for Cannibalize in the fact they dont do fast/much Direct Damage... one of the magi's complained "This would bring us in line with wizard dps!"  
<br />

<br />

<br />
The prupose of the spell is to "Reclaim <b>SOME</b> mana used in the creation of the pet"   not to "Reclaim MORE mana then it cost to make the pet"
<br />

<br />

<br />
It's like a trade skill bug, spend 5pp, gain 80pp... do you let it stay, or nerf it ?
<br />

<br />

<br />
and the magi who thinks this will nerf desirability of magi's in groups....
<br />

<br />
-I've never grouped with a magi who canni'd pets
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Another magi mentioned:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Rhasin Firestorm wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I believe the exact words used by SoE in reguards to pet cani were this:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>RWaters wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Rwaters: Pet canni was not intended by the designers, but it's not considered exploit to do it and it's not on the current agenda of the developers to change it. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Link from Sept 4, 2003 Posting, Source: <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=7321&amp;highlight=pet+cani" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dev Chat</a> from this board.</span></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Translation, at that time, they did not feel compelled to make the change. Guess what? That was a while ago. With all the touting of how much mana per tick one could get back, they might have said enough is enough, and to be rid of it all.
<br />

<br />
This does open the possibility for better improvements, and maybe this will get the lot of you content to cani away off your rears to get some other things fixed. Don't just up and compare what a beastlord and necro can do to what a magician can do. Hell, a necro can do a whole crapload more without a pet than they can with, but that doesn't mean they come close to it if they had to fight like we do.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Its basically a 'nerf' they dont like because it debunks them from the 'best pet class' position.. wish they'd just accept their role as a Pet/DD/item class, as necro's accept their Pet/DoT/twitch role, and we our Pet/Melee/Slow role
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Pet canni sucks and is dumb for a host of reasons. 
<br />
200+ mana regen...like HELLO! that's unbalanced as hell, remember "God Rods"? 
<br />

<br />
But...mages' mana regen is the worst of all the int casters. That can't be addressed so long as pet canni remains. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
There's the basic problem, restated probably more accuratly... Magi's mana regen is horrible without pet canni, and they want a <span style="font-weight: bold">BIG</span> compensation for having to '<span style="font-style: italic">suffer</span>' the '<span style="font-style: italic">nerfing</span>' of the <span style="font-weight: bold">oversight/bug</span> by the developers, which they actually decided not to <span style="font-weight: bold">Absor Smash</span> the day they found it...
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
All in all, it looks like a class-envy oriented problem, magi's have grown attached to it even though there was warnings of it being nerfed... most similar thing i can think of in relation to beastlords is the pet size problems.. we all were attached to our pets, and their size.. and when they ended up nerfing them due to a new found problem, we were all disappointed.. and initially quiet angry.. in time though we calmed down quiet a bit...
<br />

<br />

<br />
Sure it's not something that hurts our functionality, but abusing of bugs as a class' defining ability isn't something to be proud of.. I'd like to see pet canni removed, but a substitute put in.. perhaps a self-only mod rod that's more efficent.. and maybe non-lore  (allowing a magi to save 2 bags full, and use them for the full mana gain without spending mana to summon them--good for raids, or groups.. can make the rods while LFG/preping for raid, then use them later...)
<br />

<br />

<br />
This thread is border-line class balance, but since it's about magi's ill let it sit here...  (though also be careful not to simply rant about the subject)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
