				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kanne: Dead link
<br />

<br />
Kryq: Wouldn't it be better if they were given some -other- way to gain mana, that doesn't go against the point of the spells?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Summoning a pet -- designed to aid the mage, and do melee dps
<br />
Reclaim energy -- designed to return SOME (not all), of the mana used by the summoning of the pet...
<br />

<br />

<br />
I'd rather see a new spell/spell line for regaining mana, if anything... but magi's already can foci more than half their spells with reduced mana costs, and increased damage outputs, in a sense they already have their 'harvest' equivilant.. but since it's tradable, and obtainable by other wizards and beastlords.. i guess it isn't enough...
<br />

<br />

<br />
So, I'd rather see a 'proper' solution to this.. unlike the Necro Lich bug, the Lich spell is DESIGNED to return mana, at the cost of HP.. the ratio was off, but the spell did it's proper function, and wasn't nearly even 15 mana/tick more than intended, let alone 100+..
<br />

<br />

<br />
I think some form of mana regen should be give in return, but not something spectacular like 50% slow, or other outragous requests irate magi's are ranting for in class-envy posts demanding that be their compensation for this unjust nerf...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
