				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This shouldn't hurt more then then when the Beastlords had to give up the unintended Complete pet-Heal they had a long while back.
<br />

<br />
For those new to the Beastlord-class: before Warders became the summoned pets that they are now, you had to "level-buff" your (permanent, in those days) Warder, to make it powerfull. This Level-buff also reset the warders hitpoints to full, and thus was used as a complete Heal, though one with a looong casting time. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Obviously NOT intended (considering the fact that we also got very nice petheals, that many never used) so at a certain time it was fixed ( I think when the pets became summoned).  Was to be expected and only those that had come to rely on this as a battletactic hurted some.  Not much uproar about it though.
<br />

<br />
I have a 49 Mage also, and I never could understand why pet-canni was still in the game. If it was intended you sure had to go through a lot of trouble to make it worth your while (as in be high level, have focus items, AA's and so forth).
<br />

<br />
I think mages should have seen this coming, though you could wonder why SOE let it be for so long.<br />_________________<br />Bulge Trollson and Bulgette Trollson-V'Retta
