				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, to avoid any flames, I have both a 63 beast (45aa) and a 62 mage (48aa), as well as many 51+ toons, so I can say with some authority many of the beastlords here don't know what the hell they are talking about.
<br />

<br />
First of all pet canni is NOT a bug.  The formula for a reclaim is aprrox 10hp for 1 mana in return.  Mages could get a bit of mana back with conj spec and the 49 earth pet (before the expansions).  Things got better with an focus items and aa.  So those Beasties saying it is a bug it isn't.  Perhaps things evoloved over the expansions to make pet canni "overbalancing", but I disagree.  It certainly isn't any more unbalancing than slow.
<br />

<br />
My beastlord can do things my mage could only dream of, and now with pet canni being nerfed, the solo mage is pretty much screwed.  He can still do it, but the downtime is gonna be horrible.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and the complete pet heal bug that beasties had was nowhere near this.  I didn't have a beastlord then, but didn't you pretty much have to rebuff the pet?  Hell, as a former mage BE GLAD this happened.  You can now chaincast pets with another class (mage or another beastlord) and do nothing but send pets in.....if you have not tried it, do so.  You'd be surprised what you 2 chars can kill this way......
<br />

<br />

<br />
I am also ashamed of a lot of my fellow beastlords who like to comment without knowing what in the hell the are talking about.  Don't bash a class or pretend to know what you are talking about without PLAYING that class to at least lvl 60.  At lvl 49 mages were king of the world, then at lvl 60 they pretty much sucked (and yes mages were intended to be the "pet" class just look at the epic, it summoned a awsome pet).  When they put in the 61 65 pets mages again were an ok class (with pet canni)
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
IF you are on quellious feel free to send a tell to gatorbaiter my beastie, never on with the mage anymore except to summon items for the pet.....  (mallius, it anyone remembers him)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
